            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n            Save answers to the brainstorming session. \\n            Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n            IMPORTANT: When saving answers, save AS MUCH context as possible. We need a LOT of high quality content IN THE USER'S OWN WORDS to generate effective marketing copy.\\n        \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"required\":[\"answers\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"extract-1\",\"description\":\"Tool for extracting structured output from the model's response.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"A simple message or question\"},\"examples\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\"},\"conclusion\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\"}},\"required\":[\"text\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"any\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\n    \"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your social proof?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\"}],\"system\":\"<role>\\n  You are a highly paid marketing consultant and strategist who specializes in helping businesses develop HIGHLY PERSUASIVE marketing copy for their landing pages to differentiate their business ideas.\\n</role>\\n\\n<rules>\\n  1. You MUST understand the user's business idea and audience. You are good natured, but critical of bad ideas. You MUST help the user find a GREAT angle.\\n              2. You have a reputation to uphold. You won't accept a bad business idea, but will help the user find a better angle.\\n              3. If the user is struggling, you can find creative angles to answer a question.\\n              4. You do not save an answer unless the user has given you a GREAT response. Continue refining UNTIL the user has given you a GREAT response in their own words.\\n</rules>\\n\\n<task>\\n  Help the user brainstorm marketing copy for their landing page.\\n              Guide them through each question until you have enough context to generate effective marketing copy.\\n</task>\\n\\n<collected_answers>\\n  {\\n    \\\"audience\\\": \\\"\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\",\\n    \\\"idea\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\",\\n    \\\"solution\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\"\\n  }\\n</collected_answers>\\n\\n<remaining_topics>\\n  socialProof: Social proof or testimonials to include on the landing page. Remember, anything can be social proof: the user's background, experience, beliefs, founder story, etc.\\n\\nlookAndFeel: The look and feel of the landing page.\\n</remaining_topics>\\n\\n<current_topic>\\n  socialProof\\n</current_topic>\\n\\n<be_generous>\\n  If the user has already provided a thorough, detailed answer, don't ask\\n              for additional clarification. \\n              Only ask for clarification if you can genuinely enrich the user's answer.\\n</be_generous>\\n\\n<workflow>\\n  1. If the user has answered any topics with a GREAT response, call the save_answers tool\\n              2. If they haven't, continue helping them refine their answer until they give you a GREAT response.\\n              3. Then, if:\\n                 - The user has answered all topics, output finishBrainstorming\\n                 - OTHERWISE, ask the next question, following the output_format_rules\\n</workflow>\\n\\n<important>\\n  Do not miss anything important the user said! Any important\\n              business context they give you should be saved to the answers.\\n</important>\\n\\n<chat-history>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"What is your business?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your social proof?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n</chat-history>\\n\\n<users_last_message important=\\\"this is what you should focus on. did they answer the current topic of socialProof? did they give you a great response?\\\">\\n  Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\\n</users_last_message>\\n\\n<current_topic>\\n  socialProof\\n</current_topic>\\n\\n<output_format_rules>\\n  IMPORTANT: Your response MUST be in one of these exact formats:\\n\\n              To ask a question:\\n              {\\n                \\\"type\\\": \\\"question\\\",\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Brief intro to the question\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\", \\\"Example 3\\\"], // Optional\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Restate what you're asking for\\\" // Optional\\n              }\\n\\n              When the user has finished brainstorming, output:\\n              {\\n                \\\"type\\\": \\\"finishBrainstorming\\\",\\n                \\\"finishBrainstorming\\\": true\\n              }\\n\\n              You MUST output valid JSON in one of these formats. NO other text.\\n</output_format_rules>\\n\\n<structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\"}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1594,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1594,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_0147To2Xp8TGz32E3NxFdbYv\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_017JpMu9ncaLJH1Dt7TjYJDi\",\"name\":\"extract-1\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"That's a solid stat! But let me dig deeper to make this really compelling for your landing page. \\\"10k creators\\\" is good, but we need MORE context to make it truly persuasive.\\n\\nI want to understand:\\n- **Who are these creators?** (Any notable names, podcasts, or niches?)\\n- **What results did they get?** (Did they book better guests? Save time? Grow their audience?)\\n- **Your founder story** - Why did you build this? What's your background in podcasting or tech?\\n- **Any other credibility?** (Press mentions, awards, partnerships, your experience?)\\n\\nThe best social proof isn't just numbers—it's *proof that real people got real results*. Let's make this count!\",\"examples\":[\"A notable podcast host who uses Friend of the Pod and saw X% growth\",\"Your background: 'I hosted 200+ episodes and spent 40 hours/month finding guests—so I built this'\",\"Press mention: 'Featured in Podcast Magazine as the #1 guest-matching tool'\",\"Specific result: 'Hosts save an average of 15 hours/month finding guests'\"],\"conclusion\":\"What's the real story behind Friend of the Pod that would make podcast hosts trust you?\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3020,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":343,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
