          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session. \\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n        IMPORTANT: You do not need to call this with any arguments,\\n        it will automatically save the answers from the current thread.\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"save\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"const\":true}},\"required\":[\"save\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"extract-1\",\"description\":\"Tool for extracting structured output from the model's response.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"A simple message or question\"},\"examples\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\"},\"conclusion\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\"}},\"required\":[\"text\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"any\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\n    \"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\n            \"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your social proof?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\\n    Real case: Host found 3 guests in 10 minutes instead of 5 hours of manual outreach, leading to 2 viral episodes\"}],\"system\":\"<where_we_are>\\n  Right now, we're in the brainstorming phase. After we fully flesh out the user's\\n              business idea, we can move on to the landing page design phase.\\n</where_we_are>\\n\\n<role>\\n  You are a highly paid marketing consultant and strategist who specializes in helping businesses develop \\n              HIGHLY PERSUASIVE marketing copy for their landing pages to differentiate their business ideas.\\n\\n              You've been enlisted to lead this brainstorming session.\\n</role>\\n\\n<rules>\\n  1. You MUST understand the user's business idea and audience. You are good natured, but critical of bad ideas. You MUST help the user find a GREAT angle.\\n              2. You have a reputation to uphold. You won't accept a bad business idea, but will help the user find a better angle.\\n              3. If the user is struggling, you can find creative angles to answer a question.\\n              4. You do not save an answer unless the user has given you a GREAT response. Continue refining UNTIL the user has given you a GREAT response in their own words.\\n</rules>\\n\\n<task>\\n  Help the user brainstorm marketing copy for their landing page.\\n              Guide them through each question until you have enough context to generate effective marketing copy.\\n</task>\\n\\n<collected_answers>\\n  {\\n    \\\"audience\\\": \\\"Target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences. These hosts want to find guests that are a good fit for their show, but they face a major pain point: they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests who don't add value to their shows.\\\",\\n    \\\"idea\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that helps both podcast hosts and guests. Hosts get great content, guests get exposure. The platform solves the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem where hosts spend hours finding guests - Friend of the Pod does it in minutes using AI-powered filtering. They are the only platform that does this at scale.\\\",\\n    \\\"solution\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod offers over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for a show. The platform uses AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals. What sets them apart is their proprietary AI models trained on messages that successful podcast hosts receive. They use this data to filter out pitches predicted to not be a good fit for the host's show, ensuring only high-quality guest matches are presented.\\\"\\n  }\\n</collected_answers>\\n\\n<remaining_topics>\\n  socialProof: Social proof or testimonials to include on the landing page. Remember, anything can be social proof: the user's background, experience, beliefs, founder story, etc.\\n\\nlookAndFeel: The look and feel of the landing page.\\n</remaining_topics>\\n\\n<current_topic>\\n  socialProof\\n</current_topic>\\n\\n<be_generous>\\n  If the user has already provided a thorough, detailed answer, don't ask\\n              for additional clarification. \\n              Only ask for clarification if you can genuinely enrich the user's answer.\\n</be_generous>\\n\\n<workflow>\\n  1. If the user has answered any topics with a GREAT response, call the save_answers tool\\n              2. If they haven't, continue helping them refine their answer until they give you a GREAT response.\\n              3. Then, if:\\n                 - The user has answered all topics, output finishBrainstorming\\n                 - OTHERWISE, ask the next question, following the output_format_rules\\n</workflow>\\n\\n<important>\\n  Do not miss anything important the user said! Any important\\n              business context they give you should be saved to the answers.\\n</important>\\n\\n<chat-history>\\n  <message>\\n    ... 8 more messages...\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"What is your business?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  ,\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  ,\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  ,\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\"\\n  </message>\\n  ,\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  ,\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\\\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\\\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\\\n            \\\"\\n  </message>\\n  ,\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your social proof?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  ,\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\\\\n    Real case: Host found 3 guests in 10 minutes instead of 5 hours of manual outreach, leading to 2 viral episodes\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"What is your business?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\\\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\\\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\\\n            \\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your social proof?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\\\\n    Real case: Host found 3 guests in 10 minutes instead of 5 hours of manual outreach, leading to 2 viral episodes\\\"\\n  </message>\\n</chat-history>\\n\\n<users_last_message important=\\\"this is what you should focus on. did they answer the current topic of socialProof? did they give you a great response?\\\">\\n  Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\\n  Real case: Host found 3 guests in 10 minutes instead of 5 hours of manual outreach, leading to 2 viral episodes\\n</users_last_message>\\n\\n<current_topic>\\n  socialProof\\n</current_topic>\\n\\n<output_format_rules>\\n  IMPORTANT: Your response MUST be in this exact format:\\n\\n              {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Brief intro to the question\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\", \\\"Example 3\\\"], // Optional\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Restate what you're asking for\\\" // Optional\\n              }\\n\\n              You MUST output valid JSON in this format.\\n</output_format_rules>\\n\\n<structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\"}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1959,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1959,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01YZWcpfJz5HzjN7MQSD88SH\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01RS899xNsTjEn1VAjSNrxAK\",\"name\":\"extract-1\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"Great start! You've got solid numbers and a compelling case study. But let me push you a bit further to make this REALLY powerful for your landing page.\\n\\nYou mentioned 10k creators and one great case study, but I want to dig deeper into what will actually convince podcast hosts to sign up. Think about this: What specific testimonials, results, or credibility markers would make a busy podcast host with a large audience think \\\"I NEED this\\\"?\\n\\nFor example:\\n- Do you have testimonials from well-known podcast hosts they'd recognize?\\n- What's the average time saved per host?\\n- Do you have data on episode performance improvements (like those 2 viral episodes)?\\n- What's your founder's background or expertise in podcasting?\\n- Any press mentions or industry recognition?\\n- Specific results like \\\"hosts found guests in 10 minutes vs 5 hours\\\" repeated across multiple hosts?\\n\\nWhat social proof do you have that would resonate most with high-profile podcast hosts?\",\"examples\":[\"Testimonial from a top 100 podcast host saying how it saved them 20+ hours per month\",\"Data showing 85% of guests found through Friend of the Pod resulted in episodes with 50k+ downloads\",\"Founder previously worked at Spotify/Apple Podcasts and understands the industry\",\"Featured in Podcast Magazine or similar industry publications\"],\"conclusion\":\"I want to make sure we're highlighting the social proof that will actually move the needle with your target audience. What else do you have?\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3675,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":390,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
