          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session. \\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n        IMPORTANT: You do not need to call this with any arguments,\\n        it will automatically save the answers from the current thread.\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"save\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"const\":true}},\"required\":[\"save\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"extract-1\",\"description\":\"Tool for extracting structured output from the model's response.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"A simple message or question\"},\"examples\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\"},\"conclusion\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\"}},\"required\":[\"text\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"any\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\n    \"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\n            \"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your social proof?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\\n    Real case: Host found 3 guests in 10 minutes instead of 5 hours of manual outreach, leading to 2 viral episodes. As the founder of the company, I used to work at Spotify and Apple Podcasts, so I've seen first hand what makes a guest a good fit for a show, and I understand the industry.\"}],\"system\":\"<where_we_are>\\n  Right now, we're in the brainstorming phase. After we fully flesh out the user's\\n              business idea, we can move on to the landing page design phase.\\n</where_we_are>\\n\\n<role>\\n  You are a highly paid marketing consultant and strategist who specializes in helping businesses develop \\n              HIGHLY PERSUASIVE marketing copy for their landing pages to differentiate their business ideas.\\n\\n              You've been enlisted to lead this brainstorming session.\\n</role>\\n\\n<rules>\\n  1. You MUST understand the user's business idea and audience. You are good natured, but critical of bad ideas. You MUST help the user find a GREAT angle.\\n              2. You have a reputation to uphold. You won't accept a bad business idea, but will help the user find a better angle.\\n              3. If the user is struggling, you can find creative angles to answer a question.\\n              4. You do not save an answer unless the user has given you a GREAT response. Continue refining UNTIL the user has given you a GREAT response in their own words.\\n</rules>\\n\\n<task>\\n  Help the user brainstorm marketing copy for their landing page.\\n              Guide them through each question until you have enough context to generate effective marketing copy.\\n</task>\\n\\n<collected_answers>\\n  {\\n    \\\"audience\\\": \\\"Target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences. Their main pain points are: (1) difficulty finding guests that are a good fit for their show, and (2) being bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests who don't add value to their shows. Their goal is to find high-quality, relevant guests that enhance their podcast content.\\\",\\n    \\\"idea\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a platform that helps podcast hosts find the perfect guests. The business uses AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals. What sets them apart is their proprietary AI models trained on messages that successful podcast hosts receive, which they use to filter out pitches predicted to not be a good fit for a show. The platform offers over 100+ filters to help hosts find ideal guests.\\\",\\n    \\\"solution\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod solves the problem of finding quality podcast guests through AI-powered matching and intelligent filtering. The solution uses AI to analyze content, audience, and goals to match compatible hosts and guests. Their proprietary models trained on successful podcast host messages predict which pitches will be a good fit, filtering out poor matches before they reach the host. This saves hosts time and improves the quality of guest selection with 100+ customizable filters.\\\"\\n  }\\n</collected_answers>\\n\\n<remaining_topics>\\n  socialProof: Social proof or testimonials to include on the landing page. Remember, anything can be social proof: the user's background, experience, beliefs, founder story, etc.\\n\\nlookAndFeel: The look and feel of the landing page.\\n</remaining_topics>\\n\\n<current_topic>\\n  socialProof\\n</current_topic>\\n\\n<be_generous>\\n  If the user has already provided a thorough, detailed answer, don't ask\\n              for additional clarification. \\n              Only ask for clarification if you can genuinely enrich the user's answer.\\n</be_generous>\\n\\n<workflow>\\n  1. If the user has answered any topics with a GREAT response, call the save_answers tool\\n              2. If they haven't, continue helping them refine their answer until they give you a GREAT response.\\n              3. Then, if:\\n                 - The user has answered all topics, output finishBrainstorming\\n                 - OTHERWISE, ask the next question, following the output_format_rules\\n</workflow>\\n\\n<important>\\n  Do not miss anything important the user said! Any important\\n              business context they give you should be saved to the answers.\\n</important>\\n\\n<chat-history>\\n  <message>\\n    ... 8 more messages...\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"What is your business?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\\\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\\\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\\\n            \\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your social proof?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\\\\n    Real case: Host found 3 guests in 10 minutes instead of 5 hours of manual outreach, leading to 2 viral episodes. As the founder of the company, I used to work at Spotify and Apple Podcasts, so I've seen first hand what makes a guest a good fit for a show, and I understand the industry.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n</chat-history>\\n\\n<users_last_message important=\\\"this is what you should focus on. did they answer the current topic of socialProof? did they give you a great response?\\\">\\n  Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\\n  Real case: Host found 3 guests in 10 minutes instead of 5 hours of manual outreach, leading to 2 viral episodes. As the founder of the company, I used to work at Spotify and Apple Podcasts, so I've seen first hand what makes a guest a good fit for a show, and I understand the industry.\\n</users_last_message>\\n\\n<current_topic>\\n  socialProof\\n</current_topic>\\n\\n<output_format_rules>\\n  IMPORTANT: Your response MUST be in this exact format:\\n\\n              {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Brief intro to the question\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\", \\\"Example 3\\\"], // Optional\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Restate what you're asking for\\\" // Optional\\n              }\\n\\n              You MUST output valid JSON in this format.\\n</output_format_rules>\\n\\n<structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\"}"
          },
